<div id="review_1430680674" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1430680674" />
    <a title="Tania" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6450088-tania"><img alt="Tania" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1643956015p2/6450088.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1430680674?book_show_action=true">Nov 01, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tania" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tania" href="/user/show/6450088-tania">Tania</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6450088-tania?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6450088-tania?shelf=bookclub">bookclub</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1430680674" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5896102971475097523"><blockquote>The churches became Rwanda&apos;s gas chambers.</blockquote><br/>This is one of the most upsetting and shocking books I&apos;ve ever read. Because the author share his experiences in the form of a story you get to know all the people, which had an even bigger impact on me than reading the non-fictional account in <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/439799.We_Wish_to_Inform_You_That_Tomorrow_We_Will_Be_Killed_with_Our_Families_Stories_from_Rwanda' title='We Wish to Inform You That Tomorrow We Will Be Killed with Our Families Stories from Rwanda by Philip Gourevitch' rel='nofollow noopener'>We Wish to Inform You That Tomorrow We Will Be Killed with Our Families: Stories from Rwanda</a>, which sometimes felt almost overwhelming in its scope. He also writes the most horrific scenes without any sentiment or</span>
  <span id="freeText5896102971475097523" style="display:none"><blockquote>The churches became Rwanda's gas chambers.</blockquote><br />This is one of the most upsetting and shocking books I've ever read. Because the author share his experiences in the form of a story you get to know all the people, which had an even bigger impact on me than reading the non-fictional account in <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/439799.We_Wish_to_Inform_You_That_Tomorrow_We_Will_Be_Killed_with_Our_Families_Stories_from_Rwanda" title="We Wish to Inform You That Tomorrow We Will Be Killed with Our Families Stories from Rwanda by Philip Gourevitch" rel="nofollow noopener">We Wish to Inform You That Tomorrow We Will Be Killed with Our Families: Stories from Rwanda</a>, which sometimes felt almost overwhelming in its scope. He also writes the most horrific scenes without any sentiment or hysterics. An extremely uncomfortable read, but a reminder of the terrible as well as the courageous deeds people are capable of.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="5896102971475097523" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

