        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer163151737" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10147656846610725929">The story itself in this book is mediocre. I didn&apos;t really connect with any of the characters until about 3/4 of the way through.<br/><br/>The subject matter in this book is...tragic...heart-breaking...mind-numbing...made-me-sob...unbelievable-until-you-know-it-really-happened.<br/><br/>The last 1/4 of the book is horrendous in a way that I was not prepared for. It broke me. I sobbed uncontrollably for a situation that a vast majority of the world has never even heard of. My heart broke to think of the public humil</span>
  <span id="freeText10147656846610725929" style="display:none">The story itself in this book is mediocre. I didn't really connect with any of the characters until about 3/4 of the way through.<br /><br />The subject matter in this book is...tragic...heart-breaking...mind-numbing...made-me-sob...unbelievable-until-you-know-it-really-happened.<br /><br />The last 1/4 of the book is horrendous in a way that I was not prepared for. It broke me. I sobbed uncontrollably for a situation that a vast majority of the world has never even heard of. My heart broke to think of the public humiliation and torture suffered by Rwanda's Tutsi women.<br /><br />I do agree with another reviewer that the portrayal of the men (African and other) seemed to be a bit unreal--sex-crazed, prostitute-loving, AIDS-ignorant beasts really. I have to imagine that not ALL men in that area at that time were like that.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10147656846610725929" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


